<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n14076d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14076d">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14076d"> 76(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ragnar / Lodbrog <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Besides these Viking leaders, who were active in the Low Countries, we have the names of several others who were busy in France itself. The most famous of these were the sons of <mark>Ragnarr Lo&eth;br&oacute;k</mark>. Berno, who first appeared on the Seine in 855, was Bj&ouml;rn Ironside, while it is quite possible that the Sidroc who accompanied him was Sigurd Snake-eye, another son of that famous leader. With Bj&ouml;rn, at least according to Norman tradition, came Hastingus (O.N. H&aacute;steinn), his foster-father. <small> Allen Mawer, <a name="AMTV1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMTV1"><cite title="source">The Vikings</cite></a>, (1913) 44</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n14135b" href="n14all.htm#n14135b">N14 (VI.B.7):135(b)</a>. Copied by George Joyce into <a name="sa0151w" href="saall.htm#sa0151w">SA (VI.A):0151(w)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
